children.name: formatDate
children.defaultValue:
(toLocaleDateStringSupportsOptions()
  ? (dateObj: Date, locales: string) =>
      dateObj.toLocaleDateString(locales, {
        year: "numeric",
        month: "long",
        day: "numeric",
      })
  : (dateObj: Date) => fecha.format(dateObj, "mediumDate"))

children.name: formatDateTime
children.defaultValue:
(toLocaleStringSupportsOptions()
  ? (dateObj: Date, locales: string) =>
      dateObj.toLocaleString(locales, {
        year: "numeric",
        month: "long",
        day: "numeric",
        hour: "numeric",
        minute: "2-digit",
      })
  : (dateObj: Date) => fecha.format(dateObj, "haDateTime"))

children.name: formatTime
children.defaultValue:
(toLocaleTimeStringSupportsOptions()
  ? (dateObj: Date, locales: string) =>
      dateObj.toLocaleTimeString(locales, {
        hour: "numeric",
        minute: "2-digit",
      })
  : (dateObj: Date) => fecha.format(dateObj, "shortTime"))

comment.shortText: Calculate a string representing a date object as relative time from now.
comment.text: Example output: 5 minutes ago, in 3 days.
